There are also traces of polishing on one edge.

description.value: A relief object, and an entity in itself: within a raised edge is a bust of a childish Ptolemaic prince, with shaven head and side-lock, and wearing an earring. A tunic is visible by its neckline, and he apparently has a broad collar; the fingers of his right hand are shown at the lower edge. Flat back. Probably pressed into a mould or a 'trial-piece'. Buff marl ware.
